ynamics of desire and denial that permeate public spheres in our age of transnational crossings and fortified borders. Original and accessible, Passing is a timely work in light of current fierce debates over immigration, Latin American citizenship, and the US-Mexico border.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 4aMexico. 4aTijuana. 4aUS-Mexico border. 4aborders. 4aclass. 4acollectivity. 4amiddle class. 4apublic sphere. 4apublics. 4apueblo. 70(DE-601)1063111230(DE-588)4021993-8aGrenzgebiet2gnd 70(DE-601)1063883040(DE-588)4003920-1aAuswanderung2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019z978311063851608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226512075423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226512075.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-063851-6  DG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019c2016d2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles